<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-10-23T17:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-10-23T17:00:00-05:00" n="1087" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1087">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">816.00/10–2344: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in El Salvador</hi> (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Gade</hi></persName>) <hi rend="italic">to
                                the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">San Salvador</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-10-23T16:00:00-06:00">October
                                    23, 1944—4 p.m.</date>
                                <lb/> [Received 7:45 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>342. I have today received a note from the new Foreign Minister Reyes
                            Arrieta Rossi announcing the resignation of General Menéndez as
                            President and the assumption of office by Colonel Aguirre. No reply is
                            being made pending instructions from the Department.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <hi rend="smallcaps">Gade</hi>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>